{{Infobox Convention | name = Animation On Display | image = | caption = | status = Defunct | genre = Animation | venue = Santa Clara Convention Center | location = [[Santa Clara, California]] | country = United States | first = 2003 | last = 2017 | organizer = Federation for the Promotion of Animation | filing = Non-profit | attendance = 2,195 in 2012;<ref name="AC-AOD2012">{{cite web |title=Animation On Display 2012 Information |publisher=AnimeCons.com |url=https://animecons.com/events/info/2699/animation-on-display-2012 |accessdate=2018-06-25 }}</ref> 1,593 in 2005<ref name="AC-AOD2005">{{cite web | title = Anime Overdose 2005 Information | publisher = AnimeCons.com | url = https://animecons.com/events/info/684/anime-overdose-2005 | accessdate = 2018-06-25 }}</ref> | website = http://www.aodsf.org/ }}
'''Animation On Display''' was an [[animation]] [[Convention (meeting)|convention]] in [[Santa Clara, California]] at the Santa Clara Convention Center containing [[animation]] screenings, [[cosplay]], panels, guests, vendors, [[fandom]], [[comics]], [[music]] and more in reference to [[East Asia]]n and [[United States|American]] culture.
Formerly '''Anime Overdose'''<ref name="AC-AOD2005" /> and then '''AOD: The San Francisco Animation Convention''',<ref name="AC-AOD2006">{{cite web | title = AOD: San Francisco Animation Convention 2006 Information | publisher = AnimeCons.com | url = https://animecons.com/events/info/842/aod-san-francisco-animation-convention-2006 | accessdate = 2018-06-25}}</ref> Animation On Display is managed by the Federation for the Promotion of Animation and is a [[non-profit organization]]. It is the goal of the FPA to increase awareness and understanding of the art of animation and its related interests in a fun and exciting family-oriented format and to enable those interested in animation to meet and share their interests.<ref name="ABOUT-AOD">{{cite web |title=About Animation On Display |publisher=Animation On Display |url=http://www.aodsf.org/about/ |accessdate=2013-03-01 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130304112941/http://www.aodsf.org/about/ |archivedate=2013-03-04 }}</ref>
==History== The Anime Overdose convention began in 2003 at [[Santa Clara University]].<ref name="AC-AOD2003">{{cite web | title = Anime Overdose 2003 Information | publisher = AnimeCons.com | url = https://animecons.com/events/info/803/anime-overdose-2003 | accessdate = 2018-06-25 }}</ref> As the convention expanded, it was moved to the [[Nob Hill, San Francisco, California|Nob Hill]] neighborhood of San Francisco.<ref name="AC-AOD2005" /> Soon joining forces with several other animation themed groups in the area, they decided to create a larger scale event together which started the foundation for AOD.<ref name="ABOUT-AOD"/> The event was thusly named "Animation On Display" in 2007. In 2010 it moved to the Japantown area in San Francisco, where it stayed briefly.<ref name="ABOUT-AOD"/> before in 2014, moving to The Hyatt in [[Burlingame, California]] located near the San Francisco International Airport. In 2016, AOD moved to the Santa Clara Convention Center. The next year, it moved to the Marriott in [[Santa Clara, California]], its final location for 2017. On November 22, 2017, the convention announced on its Facebook page it would be ceasing operations effective immediately.<ref>https://www.facebook.com/AODCon/posts/1765160273495007</ref>
