The '''Dollar Ridge Fire''' was a [[wildfire]] that burned in [[Ashley National Forest]] in [[Utah]] in the United States. The fire was first reported on July 1, 2018. As of August 17, 2018 the fire had burned {{convert|68,869|acres|km2|0}} and was 90% contained.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://inciweb.nwcg.gov/incident/5881/|title=Dollar Ridge Fire Information - InciWeb the Incident Information System|last=helpdesk@dms.nwcg.gov|first=InciWeb developed and maintained by USDA Forest Service, Fire and Aviation Management,|website=inciweb.nwcg.gov|language=en|access-date=2018-08-19}}</ref><ref name="KSL">{{cite news |last1=Dewey |first1=Devon |title=Devon Dewey, KSL.com Before and after: The destruction from the Dollar Ridge Fire |url=https://www.ksl.com/article/46376555/before-and-after-the-destruction-from-the-dollar-ridge-fire |accessdate=August 16, 2018 |publisher=KSL |date=August 15, 2018}}</ref>
