'''Eleusis''' ({{lang-grc|Ἐλευσίς}}) was a town of [[ancient Boeotia]], on the river [[Triton River|Triton]], and near [[Lake Copais]]. Eleusis, along with the neighbouring town of [[Athenae (Boeotia)|Athenae ]], was destroyed by an inundation.<ref>{{Cite Strabo|ix. p.407}}</ref><ref>{{Cite Pausanias|9|24|2}}</ref>
