{{Infobox song contest country | Name = Kyrgyzstan | Member station = [[New Broadcasting Network]] (HTC) | National selection event = | Apps = 1 | First = [[ABU TV Song Festival 2013|2013]] | Last = [[ABU TV Song Festival 2013|2013]] | Best = | Worst = | Website = }}
The participation of '''Kyrgyzstan in the ABU TV Song Festival''' has occurred once since the inaugural [[ABU TV Song Festival]] began in [[ABU TV Song Festival 2012|2012]]. Since their début in 2013, the Kyrgyz entry has been organised by the national broadcaster [[New Broadcasting Network]] (HTC). Tola Tursunaliev has represented the nation at the 2013 festival. In [[ABU TV Song Festival 2014|2014]], Kyrgyzstan withdrew from the festival.
==History== KTRK made their debut in the ABU TV Song Festivals at the [[ABU TV Song Festival 2013|2013]] festival, in [[Hanoi]], [[Vietnam]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Granger|first=Anthony|url=http://eurovoix.com/2013/06/15/abu13-abu-tv-song-festival-2013-confirmed-in-hanoi/|title=ABU'13: ABU TV Song Festival Confirmed In Hanoi|publisher=Eurovoix.com|accessdate=15 June 2013|date=15 June 2013}}</ref>
==Withdrawal== Kyrgyzstan was not present on the final participation list that was published by the ABU. The reasons for withdrawal from the [[ABU TV Song Festival 2014]] are unknown.<ref>{{cite web|title=Line-up announced for 3rd ABU TV Song Festival|url=http://www.abu.org.my/Latest_News-@-Line-up_announced_for_3rd_ABU_TV_Song_Festival.aspx|website=abu.org.my|publisher=ABU|accessdate=19 September 2014|date=19 September 2014}}</ref>
