34518|title=Ghosts of Wayne County|last=Renner|first=James|website=Cleveland Scene|access-date=2017-07-27}}</ref> |No / Murdered |- |data-sort-value="1982-06-03"|1982 |[[Murder of Michelle Garvey|Michelle Garvey]] |14 |Michelle Garvey was an American girl who ran away in [[Texas]] on 3 June 1982, was found [[murder]]ed in [[Connecticut]] almost one month later on 1 July.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.masslive.com/news/index.ssf/2014/01/female_killed_in_1982_texas_ho.html|title='Jane Doe' found murdered in Texas 31 years ago identified as missing New London, Connecticut teen Michelle Garvey|work=masslive.com|access-date=2017-11-23|language=en-US}}</ref> |No / Murdered |- |data-sort-value="1982-07-17"|1982 |[[Murder of Krista Harrison|Krista Harrison]] |11 |Krista Harrison was murdered on 17 July 1982, in [[Marshallville, Ohio]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Hone-McMahan|first=Kim|title=New family takes in broken child.|url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-144145718.html|accessdate=15 May 2014|newspaper=Akron Beacon Journal|date=6 April 2006}}{{subscription required}}</ref> The case remained unsolved for two years, until [[Robert Anthony Buell]] was convicted of her [[murder]] in 1984.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.clarkprosecutor.org/html/death/US/buell801.htm|title=Robert Anthony Buell #801|website=www.clarkprosecutor.org|access-date=2017-07-04}}</ref> |No / Murdered |- |data-sort-value="1982-09-11"|1982 |[[Milt Pappas#Wife's disappearance|Carole Pappas]] |42 |Carole Pappas, the wife of former [[Major League Baseball]] pitcher [[Milt Pappas]] disappeared after leaving the couple's home in [[Wheaton, Illinois]]. A theory emerged that she had been killed by the [[Ripper Crew]], as a member made a confession and led authorities to a field where no remains were found. In 1987, workers drained a pond 4 blocks from the Pappas' house and found the car with Carole's body inside. It's theorized that she mistook a driveway near the pond for one leading to her subdivision, and that sh