all, Cribbs Causeway]].<ref>{{cite web|title=The Untold: Looking for DJ Derek|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/articles/1bST7mgyjTGf7SJKGBzyz1t/the-untold-looking-for-dj-derek?intc_type=promo&intc_location=news&intc_campaign=missingdjderek&intc_linkname=radio4_fac_article1|website=BBC|accessdate=19 March 2016}}</ref><ref name="DJ Derek found">{{cite news|title=DJ Derek: Tests confirm remains belong to pensioner|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-bristol-35823444|newspaper=[[BBC]]|date=16 March 2016|accessdate=17 March 2016}}</ref> Avon and Somerset Police spokesmen said that investigators were satisfied that there was nothing to suggest that the death was suspicious.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-england-bristol-35804823 |title=DJ Derek death "not suspicious" according to police |publisher=BBC |access-date=20 April 2016}}</ref> |No |- |data-sort-value="2015-10-30"|2015 |[[Death of Tiahleigh Palmer|Tiahleigh Palmer]] |data-sort-value="012"|12 |Australian girl from [[Logan City|Logan City, Queensland]], who disappeared on 30 October 2015. Her remains were found on 5 November 2015 on the banks of the [[Pimpama River]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.brisbanetimes.com.au/queensland/tiahleigh-palmer-crowds-gather-for-12yearolds-funeral-in-logan-20151113-gkywcq.html|title=Tiahleigh Palmer: Crowds gather for 12-year-old's funeral in Logan|last=Silva|first=Kristian|date=14 November 2015|work=Brisbane Times|access-date=2017-08-26|language=en-US}}</ref> In 2016 her foster father was charged with murdering her;<ref>{{cite web|work=The Weekend Australian|date=22 September 2016|accessdate=16 April 2017|author=Geoff Chambers|title=Rick Thorburn kept foster care licence|url=http://www.theaustralian.com.au/national-affairs/state-politics/rick-thorburn-kept-foster-care-licence/news-story/b2b6260d8d2c0dc319cdc665450e0bc1}}</ref> several other members of the family pleaded guilty to charges related to their attempts to cover up in the case.<ref>{{cite news|l