'''''Mr Selfridge''''' is a British [[period drama]] television series about [[Harry Gordon Selfridge]] and his department store, [[Selfridges|Selfridge & Co]], in London, set from 1908 to 1928. It was co-produced by [[ITV Studios]] and [[Masterpiece (TV series)|Masterpiece]]/[[WGBH-TV|WGBH]]<ref name="selfridgeannouncement">{{cite press release |title=Masterpiece on PBS and ITV Studios Announce ''Mr. Selfridge'' Starring Jeremy Piven |date=25 July 2012 |publisher=WGBH |location=Boston|url=http://www-tc.pbs.org/wgbh/masterpiece/media/cms_page_media/16/SelfridgeAnnouncement_3.pdf |format=PDF |accessdate=2013-10-09 |quote=MASTERPIECE/WGBH and ITV Studios have announced a coproduction deal that includes Mr. Selfridge (w.t.), a highly anticipated new drama series starring Jeremy Piven (Entourage) in the title role.}}</ref> for broadcast on [[ITV (TV channel)|ITV]]. The series began broadcasting on ITV on 6 January 2013 and 30 March 2013 on [[PBS]] in the United States.

==Development and production==
It was announced on 24 May 2011 that ITV was in discussions with ITV Studios about developing an adaptation of Lindy Woodhead's biography ''Shopping, Seduction & Mr Selfridge''.<ref name=announce /> [[Andrew Davies (writer)|Andrew Davies]] was confirmed to be working on the script.<ref name=announce>{{cite web|last=Fletcher|first=Alex|title=Selfridges story to be made into TV series |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/tv/news/a321291/selfridges-story-to-be-made-into-tv-series.html |publisher=[[Digital Spy]] |accessdate=18 February 2013|date=24 May 2011}}</ref> Beginning in London in 1908, during a time period when women were enjoying an ever-increasing amount of freedom, it tells the story of Harry Gordon Selfridge, the founder of Selfridges department store and includes members of his family, particularly his wife [[Rose Selfridge]].

It was originally planned to be screened in 2012. However, it is claimed that ITV was forced to push back airing the drama due to rival [[BBC]] airing a similarly themed drama series ''[[The Paradise (TV series)|The Paradise]]''.<ref name=store>{{cite web|last=Singh|first=Anita|title=From Selfridges to John Lewis, we've a treat in store |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/tvandradio/9562846/From-Selfridges-to-John-Lewis-weve-a-treat-in-store.html|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |location=London |accessdate=11 February 2013|date=24 September 2012}}</ref>

A set to the north of London was built to house a replica of the 1909 Selfridge's store interior. The exterior of the store was recreated in [[Chatham Dockyard|The Historic Dockyard Chatham]], in Kent.<ref>{{cite web|author=Kent Film Office|url=http://kentfilmoffice.co.uk/2013/01/mr-selfridge-2013/|title=Kent Film Office Mr Selfridge Article}}</ref> 

The disused [[Aldwych tube station]] was used to film Rose Selfridge travelling on the [[London Underground]] and scenes in the first episode.

On 8 February 2013, ITV announced ''Mr Selfridge'' had been commissioned for a second series of ten episodes, to start on 19 January 2014.<ref name=dist>{{cite web|title=Mr Selfridge commissioned for another series|url=http://www.itv.com/presscentre/press-releases/mr-selfridge-commissioned-another-series |publisher=[[ITV Plc]] |accessdate=11 February 2013|date=8 February 2013}}</ref> Anthony Byrne, who directed three episodes of series one, returned to direct some of the new episodes.<ref name=direct>{{cite web|last=Fletcher|first=Alex|title='Mr Selfridge' gets second series from ITV |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/tv/news/a457398/mr-selfridge-gets-second-series-from-itv.html |work=[[Digital Spy]]|accessdate=18 February 2013|date=8 February 2013}}</ref> On 22 July 2013, PBS also purchased a second series that aired in 2014 as part of its ''[[Masterpiece (TV series)|Masterpiece Classic]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deadline.com/2013/07/pbs-orders-second-season-of-mr-selfridge/ |title=PBS Orders Second Season of 'Mr. Selfridge' |website=[[Deadline Hollywood]] |date=22 July 2013 |author=De Moraes, Lisa |accessdate=22 July 2013}}</ref>  The second series is set in 1914 and portrays the consequence of World War I to the store and staff. On 21 February 2014, it was announced that ''Mr. Selfridge'' had been renewed for a third series, to air in 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.radiotimes.com/news/2014-02-19/mr-selfridge-to-return-for-a-third-series|title=Mr Selfridge to return for a third series|publisher=}}</ref> On 13 March 2015, ITV announced ''Mr Selfridge'' had been commissioned for a new 10-part fourth and final series.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.itv.com/presscentre/press-releases/mr-selfridge-commissioned-new-10-part-fourth-series|title=Mr Selfridge commissioned for new 10-part fourth series|work="ITV Press Centre"}}</ref>

==Casting==
An American casting director was employed to find an actor suitable to play Harry Selfridge.<ref name=lady/> [[Jeremy Piven]]'s agent informed him of the role. Producer Chrissy Skinns and director Jon Jones met Piven in Los Angeles and were impressed by his understanding of the character.<ref name=lady>{{cite web|last=Barber|first=Richard|title=The secrets of Mr Selfridge|url=http://www.lady.co.uk/culture/television-film-radio/1540-the-secrets-of-mr-selfridge |work=[[The Lady (magazine)|The Lady]] |accessdate=17 February 2013|date=27 December 2012}}</ref> Executive producer Kate Lewis was "thrilled to attract" [[Frances O'Connor]] to the role of [[Rose Selfridge]] because she had long been a fan of the actress.<ref name=notes>{{cite web|title=''Mr Selfridge'' production notes (Series 1) |url=http://www.itv.com/documents/pdf/Mr%20Selfridge%20Production%20Notes%20FINAL.pdf |work=[[itv.com]]|accessdate=22 October 2015|format=PDF}}</ref> Former ''[[Coronation Street]]'' actress [[Katherine Kelly (actress)|Katherine Kelly]] signed up to play Lady Mae Loxley and returned for Series 2 and Series 4. The casting of the trio was announced in March 2012 alongside [[Grégory Fitoussi]] (Henri Leclair), [[Aisling Loftus]] (Agnes Towler), [[Zoe Tapper]] (Ellen Love) and [[Trystan Gravelle]] (Victor Colleano).<ref>{{cite web|last=Jeffery|first=Morgan|title=Jeremy Piven, Katherine Kelly to star in ITV's 'Mr Selfridge{{'-}} |url=http://www.digitalspy.co.uk/tv/news/a373801/jeremy-piven-katherine-kelly-to-star-in-itvs-mr-selfridge.html |work=[[Digital Spy]]|accessdate=18 February 2013|date=29 March 2012}}</ref>

