==Reception==
In a poll hosted by [[MSN]] more than 80% of readers said they would continue watching the show following the first episode.<ref name=poll/> Phil Hogan writing for ''[[The Guardian]]'' bemoaned the story development. He observed that there is "so much crisis with so little drama".<ref>{{cite web|last=Hogan|first=Phil|title=Rewind TV: Mr Selfridge; Spies of Warsaw; The Polar Bear Family and Me – review|url=https://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2013/jan/12/rewind-tv-mr-selfridge-review|work=[[The Guardian]]|accessdate=17 February 2013|date=12 January 2013}}</ref> The ''[[Daily Mail]]'s'' [[Ian Hyland]] was impressed with the series and praised the performances of Piven, Tapper and Loftus.<ref>{{cite web|last=Hyland|first=Ian|title=Sold, to the man on the sofa|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/home/moslive/article-2260163/Mr-Selfridge-reviewed-Ian-Hyland-Sold-man-sofa.html|work=[[Daily Mail]]|accessdate=17 February 2013|authorlink=Ian Hyland|date=12 January 2012}}</ref> Ross Sweeney from Cultbox said that the show had direction but lacked "actual substance and any real surprises". He praised the costume designers for their "astonishing attention to detail".<ref>{{cite web|last=Sweeney|first=Ross|title=‘Mr Selfridge’: Episode 2 review|url=http://www.cultbox.co.uk/reviews/episodes/5858-mr-selfridge-episode-2-review|work=CultBox|accessdate=17 February 2013|date=16 January 2013}}</ref> Susanna Lazarus of the ''[[Radio Times]]'' opined that the character's earnestness detracted from the realism of the story. She added the female cast created the "plot tension" needed to maintain viewership.<ref>{{cite web|last=Lazarus|first=Susanna|title=Mr Selfridge review: a strong female cast but where were the visual treats?|url=http://www.radiotimes.com/news/2013-01-06/mr-selfridge-review-a-strong-female-cast-but-where-were-the-visual-treats|work=[[Radio Times]]|accessdate=17 February 2013|date=6 January 2013}}</ref> Gabriel Tate of ''[[Time Out (magazine)|Time Out]]'' branded it an unsubtle, daft series with glorious production values but felt it was "ideal escapism for a Sunday night". He also stated that the character of Agnes Towler was "the heart of the show".<ref>{{cite web|last=Tate|first=Gabriel|title=Mr Selfridge review|url=http://www.timeout.com/london/tv-and-radio-guide/mr-selfridge-1|work=[[Time Out (magazine)|Time Out]]|accessdate=17 February 2013|date=13 January 2013}}</ref> Benjamin Secher from ''[[The Daily Telegraph]]'' said that ''Mr Selfridge'' is a "less cosy, more charismatic" production of ''[[The Paradise (TV series)|The Paradise]]''. A "sumptuous, frothy drama" and "entertaining spectacle", but ultimately Secher did not believe the story.<ref>{{cite web|last=Secher|first=Benjamin|title=Mr Selfridge, episode one, ITV1, review|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/tvandradio/9781028/Mr-Selfridge-episode-one-ITV1-review.html|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|accessdate=17 February 2013|date=6 January 2013}}</ref> MSN critic Dan Owen branded it "sumptuous Sunday evening viewing". He thought the "wonderful" sets and costumes were better than those featured in fellow period drama ''[[Downton Abbey]]''.<ref name=poll>{{cite web|last=Owen|first=Dan|title=Mr Selfridge: Is it as good as Downton Abbey?|url=http://tv.uk.msn.com/what-to-watch/mr-selfridge-is-it-as-good-as-downton-abbey|work=[[MSN]]|accessdate=17 February 2013|date=7 January 2013}}</ref>

==Broadcasts==
The programme has been distributed internationally by ITV Studios' Global Entertainment brand.<ref name=notes/> ITV sold the series to a number countries at the 2012 [[Mipcom]] event.<ref name=mipcom>{{cite web|last=Roxborough|first=Scott|title=MIPCOM 2012: ITV Pre-Sells Jeremy Piven Series 'Mr Selfridge'|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/mipcom-2012-itv-jeremy-piven-mr-selfridge-377084|work=[[The Hollywood Reporter]]|accessdate=11 February 2013|date=8 October 2012}}</ref> In addition they have pre-sold the show to [[Australia's]] [[Seven Network]] and the satellite television provider, [[Yes (Israel)|Yes]], in [[Israel]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Kanter|first=Jake|title=ITV drama Mr Selfridge sold to US|url=http://www.broadcastnow.co.uk/news/international/itv-drama-mr-selfridge-sold-to-us/5044788.article|work=[[Broadcast (magazine)|Broadcast]]|accessdate=16 February 2013|date=27 July 2012}}</ref> In the Netherlands, Series 1 was aired starting August, 2013 and series 2 was aired from July 2014. In Sweden "Mr Selfridge" was aired at the public service network SVT. The last two episodes of season 4 were aired as a double on 25 June 2016 on SVT1.

